<bibRefCitation id="9657DAF1FFC52422FECEFC1E626BFC62" author="PLANCHON, J. E." box="[338,532,930,954]" firstAuthor="PLANCHON" journalOrPublisher="Bull. Soc. Bot. France" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" pagination="96 - 124" part="20" refId="ref2703" refString="PLANCHON, J. E. (1873). Sur les especes de fritillaries de France, a propos des icones et d'un manuscrit inedit de Pierre De Belleval. Bull. Soc. Bot. France 20: 96 - 124." title="Sur les especes de fritillaries de France, a propos des icones et d'un manuscrit inedit de Pierre De Belleval" type="journal article" year="1873">PLANCHON (1873)</bibRefCitation>
quotes several type localities in the Maritime Alps and only two collections (
<date id="867881C0FFC52422FFF7FC5E6099FC22" box="[107,230,994,1018]" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" value="1861-06-29">29.VI.1861</date>
, 
<emphasis id="C0B27B12FFC52422FF68FC5E6100FC22" box="[244,383,994,1018]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">
Borgeau 
<quantity id="353E0AE5FFC52422FECBFC5E6100FC22" box="[343,383,994,1018]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.7884" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" unit="in" value="346.0">346</quantity>
</emphasis>
in Herb. Thuret and 
<date id="867881C0FFC52422FDFFFC5E6299FC22" box="[611,742,994,1018]" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" value="1872-06-30">30.VI. 1872</date>
, 
<emphasis id="C0B27B12FFC52422FFFEFBBE60A9FBC2" box="[98,214,1026,1050]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Burnat s.n.</emphasis>
in Herb. Thuret). We traced in G-BU, K, MPU and FI specimens, from the cited localities, that can be considered as original material (
<typeStatus id="2D7D19A2FFC52422FEDFFBFE61DEFB82" box="[323,417,1090,1114]" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">syntypes</typeStatus>
). Among these, there is one in G-BU, which is labelled as 
<taxonomicName id="35C6DC83FFC52422FE19FBDE62D4FBA2" box="[389,683,1122,1146]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Fritillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="delphinensis" variety="burnatii">
<emphasis id="C0B27B12FFC52422FE19FBDE625CFBA2" box="[389,547,1122,1146]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">F. delphinensis</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="C0B27B12FFC52422FDCAFBDE62D4FBA2" box="[598,683,1122,1146]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">burnatii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="C0B27B12FFC52422FD2DFBDE6293FBA2" box="[689,748,1122,1146]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">manu</emphasis>
Planch. (January, 1873). The complete individual on the right is chosen as the 
<typeStatus id="2D7D19A2FFC52422FE8CFB1E610DFB62" box="[272,370,1186,1210]" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F279A700FFC52422FF14FB756139F9B9" blockId="5.[98,749,930,1698]" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis id="C0B27B12FFC52422FF14FB75610DFB39" box="[136,370,1225,1249]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Taxonomic discussion</emphasis>
. – 
<taxonomicName id="35C6DC83FFC52422FE0FFB7560EDFAD9" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Fritillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="meleagris" subSpecies="burnatii">
<emphasis id="C0B27B12FFC52422FE0FFB756211FB39" box="[403,622,1225,1249]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">Fritillaria meleagris</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="C0B27B12FFC52422FD22FB7560EDFAD9" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">burnatii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has long been confused with other close 
<emphasis id="C0B27B12FFC52422FDDCFB556212FAD9" box="[576,621,1257,1281]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">taxa</emphasis>
(in herbaria checked by us: 
<taxonomicName id="35C6DC83FFC52422FE94FAB561D8FAF9" authority="L." box="[264,423,1289,1313]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Fritillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="meleagris">
<emphasis id="C0B27B12FFC52422FE94FAB561F5FAF9" box="[264,394,1289,1313]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">F. meleagris</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="35C6DC83FFC52422FE28FAB56208FAF9" authority="All." authorityName="All." box="[436,631,1289,1313]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Fritillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="involucrata">
<emphasis id="C0B27B12FFC52422FE28FAB56237FAF9" box="[436,584,1289,1313]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">F. involucrata</emphasis>
All.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="35C6DC83FFC52422FD35FAB560B9FA99" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Fritillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="delphinensis">
<emphasis id="C0B27B12FFC52422FD35FAB560B9FA99" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">F. delphinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or fully synonymized with 
<taxonomicName id="35C6DC83FFC52422FE76FA95620EFA99" box="[490,625,1321,1345]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Fritillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tubiformis">
<emphasis id="C0B27B12FFC52422FE76FA95620EFA99" box="[490,625,1321,1345]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">F. tubiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, mostly by Italian botanists (i.e., 
<bibRefCitation id="9657DAF1FFC52422FED9FAF561C1FAB9" author="FIORI, A." box="[325,446,1353,1377]" firstAuthor="FIORI" journalOrPublisher="Firenze." pageId="5" pageNumber="28" pagination="248 - 250" part="1" refId="ref2487" refString="FIORI, A. (1923). Nuova Fl. Analitica Italia 1: 248 - 250. Firenze." title="Nuova Fl. Analitica Italia" type="journal article" year="1923">FIORI, 1923</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="9657DAF1FFC52422FE52FAF56206FAB9" author="ZANGHERI, P." box="[462,633,1353,1377]" firstAuthor="ZANGHERI" journalOrPublisher="CEDAM, Padova." pageId="5" pageNumber="28" pagination="849 - 850" part="1" refId="ref2822" refString="ZANGHERI, P. (1976). Fl. Italica 1: 849 - 850. CEDAM, Padova." title="Fl. Italica" type="book" year="1976">ZANGHERI, 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="9657DAF1FFC52422FD14FAF560E7FA59" author="PIGNATTI, S." firstAuthor="PIGNATTI" journalOrPublisher="Edagricole." pageId="5" pageNumber="28" pagination="360 - 361" part="3" refId="ref2684" refString="PIGNATTI, S. (1982). Fl. Italia 3: 360 - 361. Edagricole." title="Fl. Italia" type="journal article" year="1982">PIGNATTI, 1982</bibRefCitation>
). After study of the selected 
<typeStatus id="2D7D19A2FFC52422FE4AFAD56246FA59" box="[470,569,1385,1409]" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">lectotype</typeStatus>
and of the other available original material we are convinced that 
<taxonomicName id="35C6DC83FFC52422FDF6FA356173FA19" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Fritillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="meleagris" subSpecies="burnatii">
<emphasis id="C0B27B12FFC52422FDF6FA356292FA79" box="[618,749,1417,1441]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">F. meleagris</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="C0B27B12FFC52422FF2EFA156173FA19" box="[178,268,1449,1473]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">burnatii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an independent taxon actually closer to 
<taxonomicName id="35C6DC83FFC52422FFFEFA75609BFA39" box="[98,228,1481,1505]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Fritillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="meleagris">
<emphasis id="C0B27B12FFC52422FFFEFA75609BFA39" box="[98,228,1481,1505]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">F. meleagris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than to 
<taxonomicName id="35C6DC83FFC52422FEA4FA7561C2FA39" box="[312,445,1481,1505]" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Fritillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tubiformis">
<emphasis id="C0B27B12FFC52422FEA4FA7561C2FA39" box="[312,445,1481,1505]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">F. tubiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This hypothesis agrees with 
<bibRefCitation id="9657DAF1FFC52422FFFEFA5560ABF9D9" author="RIX, E. M." box="[98,212,1513,1537]" firstAuthor="RIX" journalOrPublisher="Bot. J. Linn. Soc." pageId="5" pageNumber="28" pagination="356" part="76" refId="ref2747" refString="RIX, E. M. (1978). Short notes (Liliaceae). Bot. J. Linn. Soc. 76: 356." title="Short notes (Liliaceae)" type="journal article" year="1978">RIX (1978)</bibRefCitation>
in considering this unit as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="35C6DC83FFC52422FD10FA5560F5F9F9" class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Fritillaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Liliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="28" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="meleagris">
<emphasis id="C0B27B12FFC52422FD10FA5560F5F9F9" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="28">F. meleagris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Anyway, further studies aimed at clarifying the taxonomic value, the systematic status and the actual distribution of this taxon are in progress.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
